  "response": "Here are some famous witty exchanges:\n\n1. Oscar Wilde Exchanges:\n\u2022 \"I wish I'd said that.\" - \"You will, Oscar, you will.\"\n\u2022 \"I can resist everything except temptation.\"\n\n2. Winston Churchill Quotes:\n\u2022 When accused of being drunk: \"I may be drunk, Miss, but in the morning I will be sober and you will still be ugly.\"\n\n3. Dorothy Parker Quips:\n\u2022 When asked to use \"horticulture\" in a sentence: \"You can lead a horticulture, but you can't make her think.\"\n\n4. Groucho Marx Wit:\n\u2022 \"I refuse to join any club that would have me as a member.\"\n\n5. Classic Movie Exchanges:\n\u2022 \"I'm not bad, I'm just drawn that way.\" - Jessica Rabbit in \"Who Framed Roger Rabbit\"\n\u2022 \"Frankly, my dear, I don't give a damn.\" - Rhett Butler in \"Gone with the Wind\"\n\n6. Sherlock Holmes Style:\n\u2022 Holmes: \"Elementary, my dear Watson.\"\n\n7. Modern TV/Movie Witticisms:\n\u2022 Many exchanges from shows like \"The Office\", \"Parks and Recreation\", and \"Friends\"\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these or provide more examples?",
